<br>
Fire and Fury and Resultion got there first.  They are far ahead of Awakened Souls and always will be.  Not that I like to keep track of this stuff, but it's true.  On that basis Awakened Souls will never be able to just screw the server from the top even if they want to, nor will any other newer &quot;uber&quot; guild.  Why?  Because with bigger and badder kids on the block, they can't do it with impunity.  And besides, it lacks credibility anyway, because they aren't the real &quot;uber&quot; guilds regardless.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Kudos to Fire and Fury and to Resolution, as I've said before, for setting a high standard up there.  Sure they've stepped on some toes (mostly each others') but it's impossibe not to in the end-game.  They ar a part of the community still, and we all see what that means.  And (I said this months ago) if any new &quot;uber&quot; guild does arise, be it AS or any other, and make it their clear policy of &quot;Screw the rest, we don't need 'em&quot; then I am positive that Fire and Fury and Resolution will be on the front lines smacking them down and keeping our home happy.<br>
<br>
Some people have a problem with large and powerful guilds at all.  I don't, it's part of the territory.  But since we are going to have uber guilds, I think we did pretty well.<br>
